.TH edoc_layout_chunks 3 "edoc 1.4.1" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
edoc_layout_chunks \- Convert EDoc module documentation to an \fIEEP-48\fR\fIdocs_v1\fR chunk.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This layout is only expected to work with \fI\fIedoc_doclet_chunks\fR\fR. Section \fIUsing the EDoc API\fR in the EDoc User's Guide shows an example of using this module.

.PP
This module breaks the convention stated in \fIedoc_doclet\fR to not rely on \fIedoc.hrl\fR in doclets and layouts. It uses \fI#entry{}\fR records directly to recover information that is not otherwise available to layouts.

.PP
\fBSee also: \fR\fIedoc_doclet_chunks\fR, \fI//stdlib/shell_docs\fR.

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBdocs_v1() ::\fR
\fB          #docs_v1{anno :: erl_anno:anno(),\fR
\fB                   beam_language :: beam_language(),\fR
\fB                   format :: mime_type(),\fR
\fB                   module_doc :: doc(),\fR
\fB                   metadata :: metadata(),\fR
\fB                   docs :: [docs_v1_entry()]}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
The Docs v1 chunk according to EEP 48.


.RE
.B
\fBdocs_v1_entry() ::\fR
\fB          {_KindNameArity :: {atom(), atom(), arity()},\fR
\fB           _Anno :: erl_anno:anno(),\fR
\fB           _Signature :: signature(),\fR
\fB           _Doc :: doc(),\fR
\fB           _Metadata :: metadata()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
A tuple equivalent to the \fI#docs_v1_entry{}\fR record, but with the record name field skipped.


.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBmodule(edoc:edoc_module(), proplists:proplist()) -> binary().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Convert EDoc module documentation to an EEP-48 style doc chunk.


.RE
